Before we can explain quantum immortality and how little time we have to make this world a better place (before the hypothetical or imagined heat death of the Universe), it is likely useful to have a Bible in handy. Be extremely careful, though; modern times call for modern languages.
&nbsp;
The Bible isnâ€™t to be taken as a tool of manipulation, carried around by corrupt lawyers, pedophilic priests and greedy prison wardens. The meaning of life, as well as the meaning of the Bible, can only be explained when you stare at death in the face. We are humans, after all, and humans are animals; biochemical robots acting out the will of their DNA.
&nbsp;
The meaning of life is the fact that life has meaning, and that our moral imperative is to always give the creatures around you a happier life. Including your own. Those who have suffered the most will always be destined for greatness. If they have truly suffered, that is.
&nbsp;
Hell could be explained as an eternal state of anxiety and confusion. The last thought you had before you died; like a movie being replayed, over and over and over; until you get to pick an alternate ending to your life. Your brain is matter and energy, after all - and matter and energy plays by the rules of quantum mechanics.
&nbsp;
This is called the Singularity. That one moment when you are most likely to die.

Went to sleep at around 10:00pm yesterday.
&nbsp;
I guess it's Judgment Day. The last day God created the Earth, or something.
&nbsp;
No more games. I need a normal life.
